HEADWORD: Operose
<hw>Op"er*ose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>operosus</ets>, fr. <ets>opera</ets> pains, labor, <ets>opus</ets>,
<ets>operis</ets>, work, labor.]</ety> <def>Wrought with labor;
requiring labor; hence, tedious; wearisome.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Operose</xex> proceeding.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Burke.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A
very <xex>operose</xex> calculation.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>De Quincey.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Op"er*ose`ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Op"er*ose`ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

